stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> maybeTimeBased : UUID UUID([long mostSigBits], [long leastSigBits])
    [*] --> NonTimeBased : UUID randomUUID()
    [*] --> NonTimeBased : UUID nameUUIDFromBytes([byte[] name])
    [*] --> NonTimeBased : UUID fromString([String name])

    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : long getLeastSignificantBits()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : long getMostSignificantBits()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : int version()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : int variant()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : long timestamp()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : int clockSequence()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : long node()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : String toString()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : int hashCode()
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : boolean equals([Object obj])
    maybeTimeBased --> maybeTimeBased : int compareTo([UUID val])

    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : long getLeastSignificantBits()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : long getMostSignificantBits()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : int version()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : int variant()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : String toString()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : int hashCode()
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : boolean equals([Object obj])
    NonTimeBased --> NonTimeBased : int compareTo([UUID val])

    note right of maybeTimeBased
        timestamp(), clockSequence(), node() are only valid
        for version 1 (time-based) UUIDs. When constructed
        via UUID(long, long), the version cannot be statically
        determined, so all methods are permitted here
        (false negatives accepted over false positives).
    end note

    note right of NonTimeBased
        timestamp(), clockSequence(), node() are forbidden:
        they throw UnsupportedOperationException because
        randomUUID() produces type 4 and nameUUIDFromBytes()
        produces type 3 UUIDs, which are never time-based.
    end note
